§7§oThis gate lets you control how a single output connects to two inputs.

The side with the taller torch is the output.

The side opposite to it is the control side.

If the control side is on, the gate will only trasfer signals from the side to the left of the control.

If the control side is off, the gate will only transfer signals from the side to the right of the control.
